On 7/23/03 9:17 PM, "Mike Soultanian" <msoultan(-at-)csulb.edu> wrote:

> Do you know if the hydro
> rods can be used with the solid lifters or are they different?

I don't know if you can use them. Anyone?

The rods are definitely different:

The push rod for solid lifters are three piece units with a hollow aluminum
core and two end pieces.

The hydraulic version is one piece steel and it's hollow all the way through
to allow oil to flow.

